title: Ground News - Overcast skies fail to dampen excitement as crowds begin to gather for New Year’s fireworks
text:
Summary by Ground News Sydney will see a return to ticket-free entry at harbour vantage points for the first time in years. Roads are already beginning to close in the CBD and near harbourside vantage points. More than one million people are expected to gather at harbour venues that are now free to enter after the government scrapped the ticketing system. Share menu More
